<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,359,744]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,431,456]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The combination of large speckled forewing, apically widening valva, and spine-like cornuti gathered in four compact clusters distinguishes 
<taxonomicName box="[684,782,468,493]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ampla">
<emphasis box="[684,782,468,493]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. ampla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1055,468,493]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[950,1055,468,493]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Stigmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
